<li id="cite_note-77"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77" title="">^</a></b> See publication of the United Kingdom Parliament position <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199697/ldhansrd/vo961218/text/61218-08.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199697/ldhansrd/vo961218/text/61218-08.htm" rel="nofollow">regarding Human Rights in China and Tibet</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-78"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78" title="">^</a></b> See Amnesty International's report on <a href="http://www.amnesty.ie/content/view/full/1683/" class="external text" title="http://www.amnesty.ie/content/view/full/1683/" rel="nofollow">violence against women in China</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-79"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFSarah_Lubman2000">Sarah Lubman (2000-03-15). "Experts Allege Infanticide In China 'Missing' Girls Killed, Abandoned, Pair Say". San Jose Mercury News (California).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Experts+Allege+Infanticide+In+China+%27Missing%27+Girls+Killed%2C+Abandoned%2C+Pair+Say&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Sarah+Lubman&amp;rft.au=Sarah+Lubman&amp;rft.date=2000-03-15&amp;rft.pub=San+Jose+Mercury+News+%28California%29&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:One-child_policy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREF.5B.5BAssociated_Press.5D.5D2006"><a href="/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a> (14 February 2006). <a href="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2006-02/14/content_520025.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2006-02/14/content_520025.htm" rel="nofollow">"China: Drug bid to beat child ban"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/China_Daily" title="China Daily">China Daily</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2006-02/14/content_520025.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2006-02/14/content_520025.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/english/doc/2006-02/14/content_520025.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 11 November 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=China%3A+Drug+bid+to+beat+child+ban&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BChina+Daily%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BAssociated+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BAssociated+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=14+February+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.chinadaily.com.cn%2Fenglish%2Fdoc%2F2006-02%2F14%2Fcontent_520025.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:One-child_policy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-81"><b><a href="#cite_ref-81" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDAyLTQyNzVfb3BuLnBkZg==/02-4275_opn.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDAyLTQyNzVfb3BuLnBkZg==/02-4275_opn.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Shou Yung Guo v. Gonzales</i>, 463 F.3d 109 (2d Cir. 2006).</a>; <a href="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDA2LTA3NjItYWdfb3BuLnBkZg==/06-0762-ag_opn.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDA2LTA3NjItYWdfb3BuLnBkZg==/06-0762-ag_opn.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Jin Xiu Chen v. U.S. Dep't of Justice</i>, 468 F.3d 109 (2d Cir. 2006).</a>; <a href="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDA2LTIzNTYtYWdfb3BuLnBkZg==/06-2356-ag_opn.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ca2.uscourts.gov:8080/isysnative/RDpcT3BpbnNcT1BOXDA2LTIzNTYtYWdfb3BuLnBkZg==/06-2356-ag_opn.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Tian Ming Lin v. U.S. Dep't of Justice</i>, 473 F.3d 48 (2d Cir. 2007).</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-82"><b><a href="#cite_ref-82" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="http://www.usdoj.gov/eoir/vll/intdec/vol24/3575.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.usdoj.gov/eoir/vll/intdec/vol24/3575.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Matter of S-Y-G-</i>, 24 I&amp;N Dec. 247 (BIA 2007).</a> (on remand from <i>Shou Yung Guo v. Gonzales</i>, 463 F.3d 109 (2d Cir. 2006/7)).</li>
</ol>
